{{Infobox language |name=Kunama |nativename= |states=[[Eritrea]], [[Ethiopia]] |region=western [[Eritrea]], northern [[Ethiopia]] |speakers={{sigfig|194,400|2}} all Kunama |date=2006&ndash;2007 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Nilo-Saharan |fam2=[[Kunama languages|Kunama]] |iso3=kun |glotto=kuna1268 |glottorefname=Kunama |script=Latin |image = Kunama.png |imagecaption = }}
The '''Kunama language''' has been included in the proposed [[Nilo-Saharan languages|Nilo-Saharan language family]], though it is distantly related to the other languages, if at all. Kunama is spoken by the [[Kunama people]] of western [[Eritrea]] and just across the [[Ethiopia]]n border. The language has several dialects including: Barka, Marda, Aimara, Odasa, Tika, Lakatakura, Sokodasa, Takazze-Selit and Tigray. [[Ilit language|Ilit]] and [[Bitama language|Bitama]] are not mutually intelligible and so may be considered distinct languages.
